  "prompt": "America is divided into how many classes of people?",
  "response": "The classification of social classes in America can vary depending on the framework used, but a common way to categorize them includes three broad classes:\n\n1. **Upper Class**: This group often includes the wealthy elite, such as top executives, successful entrepreneurs, and individuals with significant inherited wealth. They typically have substantial influence and resources.\n\n2. **Middle Class**: This is often subdivided into upper middle class and lower middle class. The middle class includes a variety of professionals, small business owners, and skilled workers. They generally have a moderate level of income and education.\n\n3. **Lower Class**: This group includes those with lower income, which may consist of low-wage workers, the unemployed, and those living in poverty. They often face economic instability and limited access to resources.\n\nSome sociologists and economists may further break these categories down into more specific groups, such as the working class, underclass, or various subcategories within the middle class. The definitions and perceptions of these classes can also vary significantly based on factors such as geography, education, and individual circumstances.",
